3 §305. Documentation timeliness; CMS alignment; exceptions
4 A. The Louisiana Department of Health shall revise Medicaid behavioral
5 health provider documentation requirements to align with federal guidance
6 stating that documentation shall be completed during the service or as soon as
7 practicable after the service is provided.
8 B. The department may establish a general documentation timeliness
9 standard. However, reasonable exceptions shall be permitted, including but not
10 limited to natural disasters, declared states of emergency, power outages,
11 technology outages, and documented health conditions.
12 C. When documentation is completed outside the general standard, the
13 provider shall include a late-entry attestation stating the date of entry and the
14 reason for the delay.
15 §306. Nursing requirement; physician equivalency
16 A. When a Medicaid behavioral health provider is required by rule to
17 maintain a nurse on staff or to maintain a written agreement for nursing
18 services solely for the purpose of medication administration, such requirement
19 shall be satisfied by the presence of a licensed physician, psychiatrist, or
20 physician assistant acting within the lawful scope of practice.
21 B. Nothing in this Section shall be construed to authorize any individual
22 to perform acts outside the scope of professional licensure.
23 §307. Medical director; inclusion of physician assistants
24 A. Notwithstanding any administrative rule to the contrary, a physician
25 assistant may serve as medical director for a Medicaid behavioral health
26 provider when the physician assistant has a minimum of two years of qualifying
27 experience in treating psychiatric disorders and is practicing pursuant to a
28 collaborative practice agreement or supervision arrangement as required by
29 Louisiana law.
